                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "n\nm",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "2n\nm",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "n\n2m",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "B"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "Either h1 or h2 for any key k every slot is equal \nlikely. \n\nEach bucket /slot is equal likely occupied. \n\nFor every slot the probability that key will be \noccupied = 1\nm \n\nExpected number of keys in the slots = \nn\nn\nm\nm\n\n=",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
